Here is the complete summary of **Preorder, Inorder, Postorder** — both **Recursive + Iterative** with **TC and SC**.

---

# 1. PREORDER Traversal

Rule:

```text
ROOT → LEFT → RIGHT
```

Example:

```text
        1
       / \
      2   3
     / \
    4   5
```

Output:

```text
1 2 4 5 3
```

---

## Recursive Preorder

```cpp
void preorder(TreeNode* root) {

    if (root == NULL) {
        return;
    }

    cout << root->val << " ";

    preorder(root->left);

    preorder(root->right);
}
```

### TC

```text
O(N)
```

### SC

```text
O(H)
```

(H = tree height)

---

## Iterative Preorder (Stack)

### Trick

```text
ROOT first
Push RIGHT
Push LEFT
```

(Left should come first → so push right first)

```cpp
void preorder(TreeNode* root) {

    if (root == NULL) {
        return;
    }

    stack<TreeNode*> st;
    st.push(root);

    while (!st.empty()) {

        TreeNode* current = st.top();
        st.pop();

        cout << current->val << " ";

        if (current->right != NULL) {
            st.push(current->right);
        }

        if (current->left != NULL) {
            st.push(current->left);
        }
    }
}
```

### TC

```text
O(N)
```

### SC

```text
O(H)
```

Worst:

```text
O(N)
```

Balanced:

```text
O(log N)
```

